{"lemma":"سُلْطانِ","slug":"سُلْطانِ","root":"س.ل.ط.ن","root_slug":"س-ل-ط-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-ط-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُلْطان","root":"سلط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":37},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20434"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, strength","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rule, dominion","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"authority","tags":["uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنْ هِيَ إِلَّا أَسْمَاءٌ سَمَّيْتُمُوهَا أَنْتُمْ وَآبَاؤُكُم مَا أَنْزَلَ اللَّهُ بِهَا مِن سُلْطَانٍ إِن يَتَّبِعُونَ إِلَّا الظَّنَّ وَمَا تَهْوَى الأَنْفُسُ وَلَقَدْ جَاءَهُم مِن رَبِّهِمُ الهُدَى","english":"These are but names which you have coined—you and your fathers—for which God has not sent down any authority. They follow nothing but conjectures and the desires of the [lower] soul, while there has already come to them the guidance from their Lord."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mandate, authorization","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"proof, evidence, an argument or case against","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a plea, an allegation, the grounds or basis for one's case being superior","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"justification","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sultan"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ل ط (s l ṭ). Cognates with Aramaic שׁוּלְטָנָא / ܫܘܼܠܛܵܢܵܐ (šulṭānā, “power”) and Hebrew שִׁלְטוֹן (shiltón, “rulership, authority”)."},"ipa":["/sul.tˤaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20434","headword_ar":"سُلْطَانٌ","root":"slT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength, might, force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saloTanapN","text_ar":"سَلْطَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd in iii. 144:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predominance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possession,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercise, of superior power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dominion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of absolute dominion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority and power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suloTapN","text_ar":"سُلْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) the former being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~uTN","text_ar":"تَسَلُّطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used as a subst.]; (Mgh;) and the latter being the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~aTa","text_ar":"تَسَلَّطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power of dominion; sovereign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruling, power;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) [in this sense, as well as in the first,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saloTanapN","text_ar":"سَلْطَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power of a king;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a governor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delegated power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power given to one who is not a king;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suloTaAnN","text_ar":"سُلْطَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) which is the only instance of this form: (Msb:) it is masc. and fem.; (M, TA;) generally masc., in the opinion of the skilful; but sometimes fem.; so say IAmb and Zj and others: (Msb:) but ISk says that it is fem. (TA.) One says, (ISk,) or some say, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDato bihi Als~uloTaAnu","text_ar":"قَضَتْ بِهِ السُّلْطَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sovereign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruling, power"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aloTanapu","text_ar":"السَّلْطَنَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decreed it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And Aboo-Zuheyr says, I heard one, in whose chasteness of speech I have confidence, say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atatonaA suloTaAnN jaAy^irapN","text_ar":"اَتَتْنَا سُلْطَانٌ جَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tyrannical sovereign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruling, power, came to us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA A^ano tasoA^ala","text_ar":"اـِلَّا اَنْ تَسْاَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA suloTaAnK","text_ar":"ذَا سُلْطَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unless thou ask the ruler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the king,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for thy due from the public treasury. (Mgh.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado jaEalotu laka","text_ar":"قَدْ جَعَلْتُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suloTaAnFA EalaY A^axo*i Haq~iY mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"سُلْطَانًا عَلَى اَخْذِ حَقِّى مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have given thee power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, to take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receive, my due from such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaw^um~u Alr~ajulu Alr~ajula","text_ar":"لَا يَوُمُّ الرَّجُلُ الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY suloTaAnihi","text_ar":"فِى سُلْطَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man shall not take precedence of a man in his authority"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, in his house, and where he has predominance, or superior power, or authority; nor shall he sit upon his cushion; for in doing so he would show him contempt. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (TA.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of winter. (TK.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An excited and predominant state"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the blood; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inflammation"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (IDrd, M, K.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blazing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of fire. (IDrd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A proof; an evidence; an argument;"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1406},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plea; an allegation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~apN","text_ar":"حُجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burohaAnN","text_ar":"بُرْهَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~ap","text_ar":"حُجَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus called because of the force with which truth attacks the mind: (B:) or, accord. to Mohammad Ibn-Yezeed, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyTN","text_ar":"سَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) signifying “ oil of olives, ” because it enlightens: (TA:) and in these senses it has no pl., because it is used in the place of an inf. n. (S, TA.) Accord. to I'Ab, it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~ap","text_ar":"حُجَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"wherever it occurs in the Kur. (TA.) But in the words of the Kur [xvii. 35],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqado jaEalonaA liwal~iyihi suloTaAnFA","text_ar":"فَقَدْ جَعَلْنَا لِوَلِّيِهِ سُلْطَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning may be either ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have given to his executor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heir,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, and power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolute authority and power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And again, in the Kur [lxix. 29],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaka Ean~iY","text_ar":"هَلَكَ عَنِّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suloTaAniyaho","text_ar":"سُلْطَانِيَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My dominion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my authority and power over men, has perished from me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my plea."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, B.) And sometimes it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A miracle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the words of the Kur [li. 38],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*o A^arosalonaAhu A_ilaY firoEawona bisuloTaAn K mubiynK","text_ar":"اـِذْ اَرْسَلْنَاهُ اـِلَى فِرْعَوْنَ بِسُلْطَان ٍ مُبِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When we sent him to Pharaoh with a manifest miracle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Az says that it is sometimes masc. because it has a masc. form; and thus it is in the last of the instances above. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ruler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like; a king; a sovereign;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a khaleefeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) these are its most common applications [in the writings of post-classical times]: (TA:) thus applied because the person so called is made to predominate; to have, or exercise, superior power or force; to have dominion, or the like: or because he is one of the evidences of God: (Aboo-Bekr, TA:) or because he possesses proof or evidence [of his right]: or because by him pleas and rights are established: (TA:) or because he enlightens the earth, (Msb, * B,) and is of great usefulness; (B;) the word being derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyTN","text_ar":"سَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying “ olive-oil ”]: (Msb:) it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolaAnN","text_ar":"فُعْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and when [thus] applied to a person, it is masc.: (Msb:) or it is masc. and fem.: (S, TA:) accord. to Mohammad Ibn-Yezeed, (TA,) fem. because it is [originally] pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyTN","text_ar":"سَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to “ oil; ” as though the kingdom shone by him; or because it has the signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~apN","text_ar":"حُجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and sometimes masc., because regarded as meaning a man; (K, TA;) or because regarded as a sing.: so says Mohammad Ibn-Yezeed; but Az observes that none beside him says this: Fr says that he who makes it masc. regards it as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he who makes it fem. regards it as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~apN","text_ar":"حُجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaATiynu","text_ar":"سَلَاطِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) It is also, itself, sometimes used as a pl.; as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idu Als~uloTaAni","text_ar":"سَيِّدُ السُّلْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", used by a poet, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idu Als~alaATiyna","text_ar":"سَيِّدُ السَّلَاطِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lord of kings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the khaleefeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lord of sovereign power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] or, as some say, the latter word is here pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyTN","text_ar":"سَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rugofaAnN","text_ar":"رُغْفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ragiyfN","text_ar":"رَغِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","ISk","M","K","Mgh","B","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}